<subSubSection id="5EBBF9D63D910C4C3305EB51F092D2B9" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="habit and habitat">
<paragraph id="D1B9FDD2B6B573C738969C697900ED72" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Habit and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D2DD3FF56A991CA25217573212D0EA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Scattered or gregarious on the bark of deciduous trees or on the rotting branch of both broadleaf trees and conifers, in summer.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BDAE91332E259F6E5F475AFE05D22121" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5778BCDFA10F80CA15E7BE20F5E1568F" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0159527C29AF6ED55B8D8553F12E1AAE" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">The Republic of Korea.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8EB4582222EEC4D2015E19CADFF8F2AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="DE78B0C3B0DA56CB0274FC57AA934BD7" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D0573ABE0B62BCEBCCDDC1BBEB5C5B5" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="F65AE7925E6FD6D64075FFF208CCF99F" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis fulva" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="D763DE27245053DAE94A689A7E23F584" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphologically resembles 
<taxonomicName id="52E1A8344D041C32400C26EDDCB29487" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. menehune" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis id="A3EFB433B3B5CB761B24A8A8EC70D0A1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0D85FF0D984E7FDE884E1395C202F4C2" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. ramealis" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="ramealis">
<emphasis id="4A01A54DE5229C90611E7141DECEA7BE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. ramealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They can be distinguished based on several morphological differences. 
<taxonomicName id="DECD29AADDDB93ED6BDF56A252A96A0D" authorityName="R.H.Petersen" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Desjardin, Halling &amp; Hemmes" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis menehune" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis id="641AFD9879EB4F93FDA2EE4E9E207C78" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a longer stipe (15-60 mm length), denser lamellae, and larger basidiospores (7.5-9.5 
<normalizedToken id="6F15D92AE66B86AE23CEFE5C2C82FBC6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4.2 
<normalizedToken id="3144423F4B6E3EEB40AB57C2F8CC6E31" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="19CE9FD83450F6A7622CAFA812752828" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="166 - 176" refId="B10" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Hemmes, DE, 1999. Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus. Mycologia 91 (1): 166 - 176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" title="Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" volume="91" year="1999">Desjardin et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4F7FD9FA0E11A4BE60B4C13EE5E38F61" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis ramealis" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ramealis">
<emphasis id="045CD48CF649670788C9DFB7B368D5A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis ramealis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a smaller basidiocarp (2-20 mm), shorter basidiospores (7.8-11 
<normalizedToken id="B78197BDD4F899DA11B9989722D465DA" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-4 mm) and different type of pileipellis (
<taxonomicName id="7B7D8F4F3EE2EC10BF0232A36433CB07" genus="Rameales" lsidName="Rameales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C7C62E8E75659EE0AA749D69B417B257" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Rameales</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-structure) (
<bibRefCitation id="90106C5E23DFCEB8A7DAC410CB51BEAF" author="Noordeloos, ME" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia-Molecular Phylogeny and Evolution of Fungi" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="31 - 49" refId="B38" refString="Noordeloos, ME, 1983. Notulae as Floram agaricinam neerlandicam - I-III. Marasmiellus, Macrocystidia and Rhodocybe. Persoonia-Molecular Phylogeny and Evolution of Fungi 12: 31 - 49" title="Notulae as Floram agaricinam neerlandicam - I-III. Marasmiellus, Macrocystidia and Rhodocybe." volume="12" year="1983">Noordeloos 1983</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="D65DF954E35057B48C95EA4D38E631AB" author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="141 - 148" refId="B9" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Perry, BA, 1997. Gymnopus villosipes -a common collybioid agaric from California. Mycotaxon 64: 141 - 148" title="Gymnopus villosipes - a common collybioid agaric from California." volume="64" year="1997">Desjardin et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
). Phylogenetically, 
<taxonomicName id="7F9D819319474C39AC7A766C1DA9A8B4" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. fulva" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="F1613D700FA126D10C5F639639A3BB4F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="9B7140CA79E0EFE2771B9E559E0C92C7" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. ramulicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="ramulicola">
<emphasis id="86C591EA2F35C7377E7B243FFF3ED972" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. ramulicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="D5E85B289C47AD5F2FE0CD3AEB078E82" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="T. H. Li &amp; S. F. Deng" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis ramulicola" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ramulicola">
<emphasis id="B5C6520A54CAE01FF79BFE9E7124F6A1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis ramulicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having a more yellowish pileus, fewer lamellae (9-12) that are brighter in color, a more reddish and thicker stipe (2-3 mm), and smaller sized cheilocystidia (23-27 
<normalizedToken id="89976F7D4D45DE141EFD30C7AE96F92B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-6 mm) (
<bibRefCitation id="301225834636E8BE78CBC1DE390B4156" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5248/131.663" author="Deng, SF" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="663 - 670" refId="B6" refString="Deng, SF, Li, TH, Jiang, ZD, Song, B, 2016. Gymnopus ramulicola sp. nov., a pinkish species from southern China. Mycotaxon 131 (3): 663 - 670, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5248/131.663" title="Gymnopus ramulicola sp. nov., a pinkish species from southern China." url="https://doi.org/10.5248/131.663" volume="131" year="2016">Deng et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
